# Bing Rewards Configuration File
# This file contains command-line options in a simple one-flag-per-line format.
# Lines starting with # are comments and will be ignored.
# Empty lines are also ignored.
# Each line should contain a single command-line flag and its value.
#
# Examples:
# --count 50
# --bing
# --load-delay 2.0
# --search-delay 5,10
# --exe /usr/bin/google-chrome
# --profile "Profile 1" "Profile 2"
#
# Boolean flags can be enabled by including them, or disabled with --no-FLAG:
# --window      # Enable opening new window (default)
# --no-window   # Disable opening new window
#
# Uncomment and modify the options below as needed:

# Number of searches to perform (overrides desktop/mobile defaults)
# Format: --count desktop_count,mobile_count
# Default: 33 desktop searches, 23 mobile searches
# --count 33,23
# --count 50  # Sets both to 50 searches

# Set if Bing is your default search engine
# Default: false (assumes Google or other search engine is default)
# --bing
# --no-bing

# Time to wait for Chrome to load (seconds)
# Default: 1.5 seconds
# --load-delay 2.0

# Time between searches (seconds). Can be single value or min,max range
# Default: 6.0 seconds
# --search-delay 6.0
# --search-delay 5,10

# Path to Chrome-compatible browser executable
# Default: "chrome" (found via PATH)
# --exe /usr/bin/google-chrome
# --exe brave
# --exe /Applications/Google Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google Chrome
# --exe "C:\Program Files\Google\Chrome\Application\chrome.exe"

# Open rewards page after completion
# Default: false
# --open-rewards
# --no-open-rewards

# Open browser in new window
# Default: true
# --window
# --no-window

# Close browser window after searching
# Default: true
# --exit
# --no-exit

# Trigger Windows IME language switch (Windows only)
# Default: false
# --ime
# --no-ime

# Chrome profiles to use (space-separated)
# Default: "Default"
# --profile Default
# --profile "Profile 1" "Profile 2"

# Run mode (uncomment one)
# --desktop     # Desktop searches only
# --mobile      # Mobile searches only
# (default: both desktop and mobile)

# Other options
# --dryrun      # Test mode - don't actually search

# Advanced search URL customization
# Default: https://www.bing.com/search?form=QBRE&q=
# --search-url "https://www.bing.com/search?form=QBRE&q="
